CC  Glyoxalase I and glyoxalase II are the enzymes lactoylglutathione lyase
CC  and hydroxyacylglutathione hydrolase, respectively. This system 
CC  detoxifies methylglyoxal and other highly reactive aldehydes. 
CC  Glutathione serves as a cofactor; variants of this
CC  pathway may occur where glutathione is replaced by another cofactor
CC  such as trypanothione in Trypanosoma cruzi [1].  
**  I found glyoxalase II by PPP vs. the glutathione biosynthesis property.
**  While glutathione import is possible, it should always be present
**  somehow. NOTE: I am seeing two different descriptions of what
**  glyoxalase I is doing: isomerizing a spontaneous gluthione adduct, or
**  adding glutathione !!.    It does both. JDS
